    "caption": "The log-dweller with a superpower most animals only dream about.",
    "shortDescription": "Salamanders look like a cross between a lizard and a frog — four legs, smooth damp skin, and a long tail. They hide under logs and rocks where the soil stays cool and wet, sneaking out at night to hunt worms and insects. Fun fact: Salamanders can regrow a lost leg, tail, parts of their heart, and even pieces of their brain."
